# Dev Server Control Rules

## CRITICAL: Server Management

### Do NOT Start Servers Automatically
- **NEVER** start `npx expo start` or any dev server unless the user explicitly asks
- The user maintains control of their own dev server
- Only ONE dev server should run at a time (the user's)

### When Fixes Are Made
- After making code changes, **ask the user** if they want to rebuild/restart their server
- Do NOT automatically start a new server
- Let the user control when and how the server restarts

### Build Commands
- Only run build/start commands when explicitly requested by the user
- If a rebuild is needed, suggest it but let the user decide

### Port Management
- Do NOT kill processes on ports unless explicitly asked
- Do NOT check port availability automatically
- Let the user manage their own ports

## Why This Rule Exists
- Multiple servers cause confusion and port conflicts
- The user needs control over their development environment
- Automatic server starts interrupt the user's workflow
